      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Did I enjoy ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "New Pokémon Snap",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "? Absolutely! Was it everything I hoped it would be after 22 years? Kind of... Nostalgia is a tricky thing where when you get what you want after so long, it just may not live up to the hype level that you'd unfairly set in your mind. While it may lack in certain areas and have a rather ambiguous point system, seeing the world of Pokémon look so beautiful deserves praise in and of itself.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
